WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:26.110 --> 00:00:28.152
l always get the shakes
before a drop.

3
00:00:30.572 --> 00:00:31.656
l had the injections.

4
00:00:34.159 --> 00:00:35.284
Hypnotic prep.

5
00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:40.123
The Federation shrink scanned
my brainwaves.

6
00:00:46.004 --> 00:00:48.423
Everything checked out.

7
00:00:49.508 --> 00:00:51.926
Doc says it wasn't fear.

8
00:00:54.221 --> 00:00:55.847
I could've told him that.

9
00:00:58.308 --> 00:01:01.644
A horse locked
in the starting gate isn't afraid.

10
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:04.439
He's just ready to run.

11
00:01:43.103 --> 00:01:44.228
A-Team.

12
00:01:44.396 --> 00:01:47.690
Our mission is to seize and control
the B-Dock area.

13
00:01:47.858 --> 00:01:50.902
clear away the bugs.
and evac the survivors.

14
00:01:51.069 --> 00:01:53.946
Now. once we land. we join forces
with the K-12 team

15
00:01:54.114 --> 00:01:57.575
at the fort. lt's a standard
grab and go. After the rescue.

16
00:01:58.160 --> 00:01:59.744
we return to the ship. take off.

17
00:01:59.912 --> 00:02:02.163
then we blow the fort
and the bugs.

18
00:02:02.331 --> 00:02:05.750
Are we clear?
Loud and clear. sir!

19
00:02:18.639 --> 00:02:21.057
Go. go. go!

20
00:02:58.804 --> 00:02:59.846
Report.

21
00:03:00.013 --> 00:03:02.390
Pretty bad.
Some of our men are in the far corridor.

22
00:03:02.558 --> 00:03:04.016
Let's get them out of there.

23
00:03:04.184 --> 00:03:07.728
Mech. we're done here. Prep to blow.
- Sir.

24
00:03:07.896 --> 00:03:12.733
Holyman and Chow. on the cover.
Biggers and Crysoch hold position.

25
00:03:12.901 --> 00:03:18.072
The rest of you. follow me.
We're on a rescue mission. people!

26
00:03:27.165 --> 00:03:29.083
Lieutenant Daugherty.
What is your status?

27
00:03:29.251 --> 00:03:32.211
Too many bugs.
No way to take back Fort Casey.

28
00:03:32.379 --> 00:03:35.464
Will hold till the john A. warden
evacuates.

29
00:03:36.008 --> 00:03:38.676
Alesia will stand by for immediate evac.
Keep me posted.

30
00:03:38.886 --> 00:03:41.053
Roger that. Mech!
What's your ETR?

31
00:03:41.221 --> 00:03:43.431
Almost there. sir.

32
00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:50.271
Done. Let's go.

33
00:04:02.326 --> 00:04:03.534
Charleston's down!

34
00:04:03.702 --> 00:04:05.786
Medic!
- I'm on it.

35
00:04:13.378 --> 00:04:15.755
Have you completed
loading the crates?

36
00:04:15.923 --> 00:04:18.799
No. That is your priority.

37
00:04:27.225 --> 00:04:28.267
Hm.

38
00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:30.603
What the hell is this about. Carl?

39
00:04:30.771 --> 00:04:32.438
Wonderful to see you again.
Carmen.

40
00:04:32.606 --> 00:04:35.858
You commandeered my damn ship.
Borrowing it. l'll give it back.

41
00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:38.736
You're never gonna take
the john A. warden from me.

42
00:04:38.904 --> 00:04:41.906
Guards. l believe Captain lbanez
needs an escort to the Alesia.

43
00:04:43.325 --> 00:04:45.618
What do you want
with my ship. Carl?

44
00:04:45.869 --> 00:04:50.122
Tsk. tsk. tsk. Carmen. that's
classified. But I can tell you this.

45
00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:53.793
This mission...
Oh. this mission will turn the tide.

46
00:04:53.961 --> 00:04:56.462
You always were
such an asshole.

47
00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:59.048
And I was always so fond of you
as well. Carmen.

48
00:04:59.216 --> 00:05:00.675
See you on Terra.

49
00:05:02.386 --> 00:05:03.970
Friends always. right?

50
00:05:18.819 --> 00:05:21.278
A-Team. reload.

51
00:05:23.699 --> 00:05:26.534
This is A-Team leader
to Fort Casey. Evacs. come in.

52
00:05:26.702 --> 00:05:28.160
About goddamn time.

53
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.871
It's a little crowded out here.
Exit now. Dock B.

54
00:05:31.039 --> 00:05:32.081
On our way.

55
00:05:32.249 --> 00:05:35.543
Show some hustle. It's quiet now.
but that ain't gonna last.

56
00:05:35.711 --> 00:05:39.130
Evacs coming out. Keep your
eyes open and your heads down!

57
00:05:39.297 --> 00:05:41.424
I don't wanna lose
anyone to friendly fire!

58
00:05:47.055 --> 00:05:48.597
Who's in charge?

59
00:05:48.765 --> 00:05:49.890
Acting commander. sir.

60
00:05:50.058 --> 00:05:52.435
Major Henry Varro
has been relieved of duty.

61
00:05:52.602 --> 00:05:54.812
Relieved?
What the hell happened?

62
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:58.524
This was a suicide mission from the get-go.
fucking head case.

63
00:05:58.692 --> 00:06:01.485
Shut your mouth. Ratzass.
You wanna be busted like Hero?

64
00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:48.491
We're out of here!
Let's get back to the ship.

65
00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:50.910
Mech! How's it coming
with that charge?

66
00:06:51.078 --> 00:06:54.038
Armed and dangerous.

67
00:07:01.880 --> 00:07:04.048
You have to be kidding me.

68
00:07:12.808 --> 00:07:15.684
Thanks for waiting. jackass!

69
00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:19.939
Command! lf there are new orders.
let me know. goddamn it!

70
00:07:20.107 --> 00:07:23.651
Are we gonna escort
the john A. warden or not?

71
00:07:33.537 --> 00:07:34.787
Behind us!

72
00:07:34.955 --> 00:07:36.455
Sir! This is Biggers!

73
00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:38.999
Can't hold any more! We're...
Aah!

74
00:07:39.167 --> 00:07:41.627
You bug sons of bitches! Aah!

75
00:07:43.255 --> 00:07:45.131
Captain jonah. This is A-Team.

76
00:07:45.298 --> 00:07:47.925
Landing ship destroyed.
Boarding directly now.

77
00:07:48.093 --> 00:07:51.178
Roger that. As soon as you're aboard.
Alesia will depart.

78
00:07:52.973 --> 00:07:56.517
Wedge formation!
Fall back into the Alesia!

79
00:08:17.873 --> 00:08:20.749
Hold formation.
Hold formation.

80
00:08:29.634 --> 00:08:33.053
My arm! My goddamn arm!

81
00:08:34.681 --> 00:08:36.557
Medic!

82
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:44.106
Four-twenty-four.

83
00:08:45.275 --> 00:08:48.152
425. 426.

84
00:08:48.653 --> 00:08:50.738
Return to the ship!

85
00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:56.160
Four-twenty-eight. 429.

86
00:08:56.953 --> 00:08:59.288
430. 431.

87
00:08:59.456 --> 00:09:02.333
Trig! Move your goddamn ass.
We're taking off.

88
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:19.475
Come on!

89
00:09:21.686 --> 00:09:23.354
Jump!

90
00:09:35.242 --> 00:09:36.325
Thanks.

91
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:38.619
Anytime.

92
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:41.038
Score?
- Four-thirty.

93
00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:42.831
Give or take.

94
00:10:12.862 --> 00:10:14.905
You gonna do it or what?

95
00:10:15.115 --> 00:10:17.157
Hit it. maestro.

96
00:10:18.576 --> 00:10:19.618
Three.

97
00:10:19.786 --> 00:10:22.621
two. one. boom.

98
00:10:30.505 --> 00:10:34.550
Oh. come on. guys.
This shit ain't over yet.

99
00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:42.516
Ha-ha-ha. Yeah. All right.

100
00:10:50.692 --> 00:10:52.985
So. what the hell happened
to you guys down there?

101
00:10:53.695 --> 00:10:56.280
We were right on top
of a motherfucking ant hill.

102
00:10:56.448 --> 00:10:57.573
Varro saved our ass.

103
00:10:57.782 --> 00:11:01.952
Then that ESP prick. Jenkins.
sent us on a death run.

104
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:03.912
Straight into
a goddamn hive.

105
00:11:04.748 --> 00:11:06.749
But you didn't hear
that shit from me.

106
00:11:06.958 --> 00:11:08.459
Uh. I'm sorry.
you say something?

107
00:11:08.626 --> 00:11:10.377
Attention!

108
00:11:15.175 --> 00:11:17.843
You can all be proud of yourselves.

109
00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:20.721
We saved some lives.

110
00:11:22.098 --> 00:11:24.016
And we killed some bugs.

111
00:11:24.184 --> 00:11:26.935
But we lost
some good troopers today.

112
00:11:27.604 --> 00:11:30.606
Here's to the dead.
And to the next man to die!

113
00:11:30.774 --> 00:11:32.274
Now let's get back to Terra.

114
00:11:32.442 --> 00:11:34.276
And we can put some real glasses
in these hands.

115
00:11:44.579 --> 00:11:46.705
Heh. Check it out.

116
00:11:46.873 --> 00:11:51.001
What's the matter? You never saw
a flanker without her armor before?

117
00:11:51.169 --> 00:11:53.921
Yeah. But they usually
look like Ratzass.

118
00:11:54.089 --> 00:11:56.256
Ratzass?
Heh. That's what they call me.

119
00:11:56.424 --> 00:11:58.717
Because you don't give
a rat's ass about anything.

120
00:11:58.885 --> 00:12:00.177
What a surprise.
Hey.

121
00:12:00.929 --> 00:12:03.972
you want me to show you
to the shower?

122
00:12:04.140 --> 00:12:06.350
I could wash your back.

123
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:10.062
You don't wanna wash my front?

124
00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:15.901
Hm.

125
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:22.449
Shh. Shut up.

126
00:12:38.633 --> 00:12:40.801
Captain on the bridge.

127
00:12:41.094 --> 00:12:44.179
Stand down. This is
your ship. not mine. captain.

128
00:12:44.347 --> 00:12:45.889
Simple respect.
Captain Ibanez.

129
00:12:46.057 --> 00:12:48.851
For what happened on Planet-P
Venta Monis alone.

130
00:12:49.018 --> 00:12:51.019
If only more strikes
were executed that way.

131
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:53.730
I had a good team.

132
00:12:53.898 --> 00:12:55.232
What can you tell me?

133
00:12:55.733 --> 00:12:56.775
About?

134
00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:58.193
Where's my ship?

135
00:12:58.361 --> 00:13:00.112
And why does Jenkins
want it so badly?

136
00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:02.906
Believe me. if I could provide you
with any information...

137
00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.909
This ship is in pursuit
of the john A. warden. isn't it?

138
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:09.246
I understand your concern for the john A. Warden.
Captain Ibanez.

139
00:13:09.414 --> 00:13:11.457
but this is the Alesia
and we command it.

140
00:13:11.666 --> 00:13:13.876
Our orders are to return to Terra.

141
00:13:14.043 --> 00:13:16.587
Then show me the data
on the john A. warden's path.

142
00:13:16.754 --> 00:13:19.548
Where's she headed?
We don't know. captain.

143
00:13:19.716 --> 00:13:23.802
We lost her signal
shortly after we began pursuit.

144
00:13:26.681 --> 00:13:29.141
Please contact me when you
find the john A. warden.

145
00:13:29.309 --> 00:13:30.350
Aye. aye. captain.

146
00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:38.942
Hey. man.
Don't write this up. okay?

147
00:13:39.110 --> 00:13:41.612
This is a serious wound.

148
00:13:43.615 --> 00:13:44.865
Could've been a lot worse.

149
00:13:45.533 --> 00:13:48.243
I can't keep something like this
off the record. l...

150
00:13:48.995 --> 00:13:51.413
I'm gonna have to take your arm.
Fine.

151
00:13:51.581 --> 00:13:54.208
But. look. at least do
what you can to make sure

152
00:13:54.375 --> 00:13:56.001
it doesn't get back to my folks.

153
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:57.920
You can at least do that.
right. doc?

154
00:14:03.343 --> 00:14:04.927
Let's do this.
Um.

155
00:14:05.094 --> 00:14:06.929
why don't we wait
till the shaking stops?

156
00:14:07.096 --> 00:14:10.682
The ship will be fine.
I'm not talking about the ship.

157
00:14:34.457 --> 00:14:36.166
Oh.

158
00:14:47.345 --> 00:14:50.639
Hey. newb. Dance class
is down the hall.

159
00:14:50.807 --> 00:14:54.017
No. It's right here.
Care to dance?

160
00:14:54.185 --> 00:14:57.980
Heh. This ring is for fighting.
Humor me.

161
00:15:00.692 --> 00:15:02.568
What's your name?
Chow.

162
00:15:02.735 --> 00:15:05.487
Well. Chow.
I don't usually dance with guys.

163
00:15:05.655 --> 00:15:07.030
but in your case. heh.

164
00:15:07.198 --> 00:15:08.907
I'll make an exception.

165
00:15:09.117 --> 00:15:12.119
Who's your money on?
Ratzass is bigger.

166
00:15:12.287 --> 00:15:14.204
Not much upstairs...
Whatever. dude.

167
00:15:14.372 --> 00:15:17.708
Ratzass gets in one good solid hit
and Chow's going down.

168
00:15:17.875 --> 00:15:19.876
Shit. if he can ever
land a punch.

169
00:15:20.044 --> 00:15:21.670
Chow's fast. man.

170
00:15:23.006 --> 00:15:27.134
All right. fighters.
to your corners.

171
00:15:29.971 --> 00:15:34.141
You back out now.
I won't think any less of you.

172
00:15:35.226 --> 00:15:38.478
When I ring the bell.
come out fighting.

173
00:15:40.189 --> 00:15:42.816
They're gonna miss you
when you're gone.

174
00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:44.026
Hm.

175
00:15:49.657 --> 00:15:51.491
Aw...

176
00:16:09.802 --> 00:16:11.511
Good thing
there's not much upstairs.

177
00:16:11.679 --> 00:16:13.472
Don't have to worry
about brain damage.

178
00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:15.641
Hey. damage this.

179
00:16:29.322 --> 00:16:30.447
Hey.

180
00:16:42.627 --> 00:16:44.378
Did you see that?

181
00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.927
Didn't know you had it in you.

182
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:57.015
Flash of inspiration. Unh.

183
00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:04.147
E057. E057.

184
00:17:04.315 --> 00:17:08.151
E057.

185
00:17:25.253 --> 00:17:27.754
Thanks. l really appreciate...

186
00:17:27.922 --> 00:17:29.339
it.

187
00:17:33.094 --> 00:17:34.136
Hm.

188
00:17:36.597 --> 00:17:38.849
They can't get me a bed
till tomorrow.

189
00:17:39.475 --> 00:17:41.685
Thanks for letting me use
the com...?

190
00:17:41.853 --> 00:17:43.311
Tia.

191
00:17:43.479 --> 00:17:46.189
Tia Durer. Trig is fine.

192
00:17:46.357 --> 00:17:49.484
Otis Hacks. Bugspray.

193
00:17:50.737 --> 00:17:52.779
Hey. uh...

194
00:17:53.156 --> 00:17:57.159
Thanks for the catch.
At Fort Casey.

195
00:17:58.494 --> 00:18:02.706
Sleeping with a gun?
You must know something I don't.

196
00:18:03.332 --> 00:18:07.961
Morita XXX sniper rifle.
Classic.

197
00:18:11.132 --> 00:18:12.215
Hm.

198
00:18:12.759 --> 00:18:15.093
You've got a nice smile
for a psych job.

199
00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:17.304
Thanks...

200
00:18:17.555 --> 00:18:19.264
I think.

201
00:18:19.766 --> 00:18:22.225
So up for a little training?

202
00:18:22.393 --> 00:18:26.021
I think I've had about all the target practice
I can stand today.

203
00:18:26.189 --> 00:18:31.568
Yeah. I was thinking about
something a little more strenuous.

204
00:18:36.949 --> 00:18:39.117
You didn't really use
the intercom. did you?

205
00:18:39.660 --> 00:18:42.162
Would you like to know more?
Heh.

206
00:18:43.247 --> 00:18:44.331
Oh.

207
00:18:50.463 --> 00:18:53.215
Everyone's doing their part.

208
00:19:06.020 --> 00:19:07.938
Major Henry Varro.

209
00:19:10.441 --> 00:19:14.694
One of the most decorated
officers in the Federation.

210
00:19:16.989 --> 00:19:21.493
You've run long-range ops
in places even God's given up on.

211
00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:28.375
What did you do?

212
00:19:28.793 --> 00:19:30.585
Why won't you talk?

213
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:32.337
And why won't your men talk?

214
00:19:52.233 --> 00:19:53.400
Heh.

215
00:19:57.154 --> 00:19:58.530
There are modifications

216
00:19:58.698 --> 00:20:01.408
you can score on the black market
when you get to Terra.

217
00:20:01.576 --> 00:20:04.119
But as far as what
the Federation will pay for.

218
00:20:04.287 --> 00:20:06.580
it's still a good prosthetic.
Got it.

219
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:10.041
Nice job. Don't know
what you were nervous about.

220
00:20:10.209 --> 00:20:13.295
I bet this looks as good
as all the others.

221
00:20:14.589 --> 00:20:17.132
What others?
You're my first.

222
00:20:17.592 --> 00:20:22.012
Matter of fact. you're the first guy
I've worked on that's actually lived.

223
00:20:26.767 --> 00:20:28.935
Every commander
I've ever served under

224
00:20:29.103 --> 00:20:31.730
tries to get me to use
a regulation gun.

225
00:20:31.898 --> 00:20:35.108
That is. until they see
how many l kill with that one.

226
00:20:35.985 --> 00:20:37.694
Then they don't ask me anymore.

227
00:20:41.616 --> 00:20:44.200
My parents made that rifle.

228
00:20:47.121 --> 00:20:49.831
There was an armory
in my home town.

229
00:20:50.082 --> 00:20:52.709
Everyone worked there.

230
00:20:56.923 --> 00:21:01.092
That is. until the bugs melted
the place with a plasma bomb.

231
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:06.222
Soldiers. civilians. families.

232
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:09.142
Everyone died.

233
00:21:11.562 --> 00:21:16.316
I swore then
that I'd kill just as many bugs.

234
00:21:18.611 --> 00:21:20.570
And I'd do it with that gun.

235
00:21:21.906 --> 00:21:23.740
That's why you count?

236
00:21:25.409 --> 00:21:28.995
No. That's why it counts.

237
00:22:08.285 --> 00:22:10.620
Goddamn you. Carl.

238
00:22:18.963 --> 00:22:22.632
Where'd you learn that haymaker?
Dance class.

239
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:26.636
Shit. l knew it. I just felt it.

240
00:22:26.804 --> 00:22:28.805
We aren't gonna see Terra
any time soon.

241
00:22:28.973 --> 00:22:32.225
Aw. you're a pessimist.
Specialist. actually.

242
00:22:32.393 --> 00:22:35.603
Well. almost.
Five points short on the ESP test.

243
00:22:35.771 --> 00:22:37.772
If one more jack
had been a diamond.

244
00:22:37.940 --> 00:22:40.358
I wouldn't be here
with you dumbasses.

245
00:22:42.653 --> 00:22:44.154
You son of a bitch.

246
00:22:44.321 --> 00:22:47.323
That's how you always know
when l'm in the shower.

247
00:22:48.451 --> 00:22:51.119
So can you tell
what I'm thinking now?

248
00:22:51.287 --> 00:22:53.329
Hell. even I know
what you're thinking now.

249
00:22:53.497 --> 00:22:55.707
You make me sick.

250
00:22:58.127 --> 00:22:59.210
Hm.

251
00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:03.548
What's up. Lieutenant Daugherty?
I thought you were in Medical.

252
00:23:04.050 --> 00:23:07.385
